10\. Security Conventions (POC Scope)

The POC operates in a single-user, local Kubernetes environment.
Production security controls are architecturally present but
implementation is deferred per the security architecture's
phase-appropriate approach.

10.1 POC Security Posture

-   No authentication on API endpoints (single-user demo environment)

-   No TLS between services (cluster-internal traffic only)

-   X-Request-ID header required for audit tracing (enforced)

-   Member IDs are logged but not masked in POC (production: masked)

-   CORS: allow-origin set to frontend service only

10.2 Production-Ready Headers (Documented, Not Enforced in POC)

-   Authorization: Bearer {jwt} --- RBAC + ABAC token

-   X-User-Id: authenticated user identity

-   X-User-Role: role claim from token

-   X-Audit-Reason: required for break-glass access

These headers are accepted and logged by the POC services but not
validated. The API contracts define them so that implementing
authentication is additive, not restructuring.

11\. Cross-Stream Integration Notes

This section documents provisional decisions and known dependencies on
other streams. Items tagged CROSS-STREAM require reconciliation when S1
and S2 produce their draft contracts.

11.1 Dependencies on S1 (Schema)

-   CROSS-STREAM: The Member response schema uses clean domain field
    names. S1 must provide the mapping from legacy MEMBER_MASTER column
    names (e.g., MBR_ID, FIRST_NM, LAST_NM, HIRE_DT, TIER_CD, STATUS_CD)
    to domain model fields (id, firstName, lastName, hireDate, tier,
    status).

-   CROSS-STREAM: The Salary endpoint returns pensionablePay and
    leavePayout as separate fields. S1 must confirm SALARY_HIST
    distinguishes these or whether they require derivation.

-   CROSS-STREAM: The service credit detail endpoint assumes SVC_CREDIT
    has a type discriminator (employment, purchased, military, leave).
    S1 must confirm column name and valid values.

11.2 Dependencies on S2 (Rules)

-   CROSS-STREAM: The calculation trace step structure assumes rule IDs
    follow the format CATEGORY-NNN (e.g., MEMBERSHIP-001,
    ELIGIBILITY-003). S2 must confirm rule ID format.

-   CROSS-STREAM: The eligibility evaluate response lists all retirement
    paths. S2 must confirm the complete enumeration: normal, rule75,
    rule85, earlyTier12, earlyTier3, deferred, disability.

-   CROSS-STREAM: Payment option actuarial factors are currently
    placeholders. S2 must provide the factor table or formula for J&S
    reductions based on member and beneficiary ages.

-   CROSS-STREAM: The benefit calculator assumes AMS is computed by the
    Connector and passed to Intelligence. If S2 determines that AMS is a
    rules-layer concern, this boundary shifts.

11.3 Dependencies on S4 (Frontend)

S4 consumes the API contracts defined here. The workspace composition
response drives component rendering. S4 needs the component registry
endpoint to enumerate available components and their expected data
shapes. The composition response includes component IDs and parameter
objects; S4 must implement a component resolver that maps IDs to React
components.

12\. Document Governance

12.1 Contract Maturity Levels

  ----------------- -------------------------- ---------------------------------
  **Level**         **Meaning**                **Usage**

  **Provisional**   Best current understanding Streams may build to this but
                                               expect changes

  **Draft**         Reviewed by at least two   Streams should build to this with
                    streams                    confidence

  **Accepted**      Technical Director         Changes require formal revision
                    approved                   
  ----------------- -------------------------- ---------------------------------

All contracts in this document are currently at Provisional maturity.
They will advance to Draft status after reconciliation with S1 and S2
outputs, and to Accepted after Technical Director review.

**End of Document**
